WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.580
Hi, my name is Travis Gerke, and I'm excited to tell you about the top three reasons that

00:00:09.580 --> 00:00:14.560
you should take the causal inference with R workshop at PositConf 2023.

00:00:14.560 --> 00:00:18.480
The first reason is that in this workshop, you will learn modern and elegant ways to

00:00:18.480 --> 00:00:23.200
perform causal inference using tools like tidymodels and the tidyverse.

00:00:23.200 --> 00:00:26.320
This contrasts with some more traditional ways of teaching causal inference that are

00:00:26.320 --> 00:00:31.280
very heavily theoretical or use more legacy programming approaches.

00:00:31.280 --> 00:00:33.360
The second reason builds on the first reason.

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:37.939
We have some fun coding elements in this workshop, such as performing causal inference with groupby

00:00:37.939 --> 00:00:38.939
and summarize.

00:00:38.939 --> 00:00:42.799
I bet you didn't think that was possible, but in this workshop, you'll find out how.

00:00:42.799 --> 00:00:44.720
The third reason, of course, is the people.

00:00:44.720 --> 00:00:48.439
Malcolm Barrett has years of experience running this workshop successfully, and I'm sure you'll

00:00:48.439 --> 00:00:49.439
enjoy it.

00:00:49.439 --> 00:00:53.200
As for myself, it's my first year with the workshop, but I'm excited to come share my

00:00:53.240 --> 00:00:57.080
experience as a student of causal inference at Harvard School of Public Health, later

00:00:57.080 --> 00:01:01.880
a faculty member in academia studying causal inference and its applied methods, and now

00:01:01.880 --> 00:01:05.120
as a practitioner in the clinical trial space.

00:01:05.120 --> 00:01:06.800
And of course, there's you.

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:12.080
Together, we'll form a small community over two days of causal inference enthusiasts using

00:01:12.080 --> 00:01:14.080
R to implement it, and I'm really excited to see you there.

